https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/pWOrn2waRpTNNpSrSkBoDm657lD.jpg 16 Years of Alcohol is a 2003 drama film written and directed by Richard Jobson, based on his 1987 novel. The film is Jobson's first directorial effort, following a career as a television presenter on BSkyB and VH-1, and as the vocalist for the 1970s punk rock band The Skids. 16 Years of Alcohol
